# CTX-INTERPRETATION: This string appears in the user manual or help section
# of the Sim4Life.lite application, guiding users on how to open an existing
# project.
# CTX-VERSION: unknown
#: services/static-webserver/client/source/class/osparc/product/quickStart/s4llite/Dashboard.js:70
msgid ""
"        4) To open an existing desktop project in Sim4Life.lite:         - "
"Click the + Start Sim4Life.lite button to create a new project.<br>        - "
"Click the menu and select “File Browser…”.<br>        - Click “Upload File” "
"for the .smash project and select the file from your desktop. Repeat the "
"same step, but this         time select “Upload Folder” and then select the "
"result folder from your desktop. Close the window<br>        - Click the "
"Menu again and click “Open” to select the file you just uploaded.<br>      "
msgstr ""
"4) 要在 Sim4Life.lite 中打开一个现有的桌面项目： - 点击 + 启动 Sim4Life.lite "
"按钮以创建一个新项目。<br> - 点击菜单并选择“文件浏览器…”。<br> - 点击“上传文"
"件”以上传 .smash 项目文件，并从桌面选择文件。重复此步骤，但这次选择“上传文件"
"夹”，然后从桌面选择结果文件夹。关闭窗口<br> - 再次点击菜单，然后点击“打开”以"
"选择您刚刚上传的文件。<br>      "

# CTX-INTERPRETATION: This string likely appears as a section title or heading
# in the documentation or user interface of the Sim4Life.lite software,
# outlining its features and limitations.
# CTX-VERSION: unknown
#: services/static-webserver/client/source/class/osparc/product/quickStart/s4llite/S4LLiteSpecs.js:22
msgid "Sim4Life.lite: Features and Limitations"
msgstr "Sim4Life.lite：功能和限制"

# CTX-INTERPRETATION: This string appears on the homepage of the Sim4Life.lite
# website, providing an overview of the platform's purpose and availability
# for students.
# CTX-VERSION: unknown
#: services/static-webserver/client/source/class/osparc/product/quickStart/s4llite/S4LLiteSpecs.js:28
msgid ""
"        Sim4Life.lite is a powerful web-based simulation platform that "
"allows you to model and analyze real-world phenomena and to         design "
"complex technical devices in a validated environment. Sim4Life.lite has been "
"created specifically for students to         facilitate their understanding "
"of computational modeling and simulations for various topics, ranging from "
"wireless communication         to medical applications. The access to "
"Sim4Life.lite is available free of charge to students enrolled at registered "
"universities.      "
msgstr ""
"Sim4Life.lite 是一个强大的基于网络的仿真平台，允许您在经过验证的环境中对现实"
"世界现象进行建模和分析，并设计复杂的技术设备。Sim4Life.lite 专为学生设计，以"
"帮助他们理解从无线通信到医疗应用等各种主题的计算建模和仿真。注册大学的在校学"
"生可以免费访问 Sim4Life.lite。      "

# CTX-INTERPRETATION: This string appears as a feature list on the product
# page of the Sim4Life.lite scientific simulation application, highlighting
# its capabilities and components.
# CTX-VERSION: unknown
#: services/static-webserver/client/source/class/osparc/product/quickStart/s4llite/S4LLiteSpecs.js:37
msgid ""
"        <b>Sim4Life.lite offers</b><br>        - Framework (GUI, Modeling, "
"Postprocessing)<br>        - 3D modeling environment (based on the ACIS "
"toolkit) and CAD translators<br>        - Postprocessing and visualization "
"of the simulation results (2D and 3D viewers, 2D planar slice, volume "
"rendering, streamlines, surface fields on arbitrary 3D structures, radiation "
"and far-field data)<br>        - No restrictions on number of modeling "
"objects<br>        - Solvers & Tissue Models:<br>        &emsp;- P-EM-FDTD: "
"Electromagnetics Full-Wave Solver<br>        &emsp;- P-EM-QS: Quasi-Static "
"Electromagnetics Solver<br>        &emsp;- P-Thermal: Thermodynamic "
"Solver<br>        &emsp;- P-Acoustics: Acoustics Solver<br>        &emsp;- T-"
"Neuro: Neuronal Tissue Models<br>        - Computational anatomical model "
"Yoon-sun, the first Korean model of the IT’IS Virtual Population<br>        "
"- Material database<br>        - Python and Jupyter Notebook scripting      "
msgstr ""
"        <b>Sim4Life.lite 提供</b><br>        - 框架（GUI，建模，后处理）"
"<br>        - 3D 建模环境（基于 ACIS 工具包）和 CAD 转换器<br>        - 模拟"
"结果的后处理和可视化（2D 和 3D 查看器，2D 平面切片，体积渲染，流线，任意 3D "
"结构上的表面场，辐射和远场数据）<br>        - 对建模对象数量没有限制"
"<br>        - 求解器和组织模型：<br>        &emsp;- P-EM-FDTD：电磁全波求解器"
"<br>        &emsp;- P-EM-QS：准静态电磁求解器<br>        &emsp;- P-Thermal："
"热力学求解器<br>        &emsp;- P-Acoustics：声学求解器<br>        &emsp;- T-"
"Neuro：神经组织模型<br>        - 计算解剖模型 Yoon-sun，IT’IS 虚拟人口的第一"
"个韩国模型<br>        - 材料数据库<br>        - Python 和 Jupyter Notebook 脚"
"本      "

# CTX-INTERPRETATION: This string appears in the limitations section of the
# user manual for a scientific simulation application, detailing the
# constraints and hardware requirements for running simulations.
# CTX-VERSION: unknown
#: services/static-webserver/client/source/class/osparc/product/quickStart/s4llite/S4LLiteSpecs.js:56
msgid ""
"        <b>Limitations</b><br>        The following limitations apply:"
"<br>        - Grid size of each simulation is limited to a maximum of <b>20 "
"million grid cells</b><br>        - High-Performance Computing is not "
"supported:<br>        &emsp;- GPU acceleration is not available<br>        "
"&emsp;- MPI multicore acceleration is not available<br>        - 3rd-party "
"tools are not available (e.g., MUSAIK, SYSSIM, IMAnalytics, etc…)<br>        "
"- Additional ViP models cannot be added<br>        - 30 minutes idle time "
"before logout<br>        - Hardware resource limits<br>        &emsp;- 3 "
"CPUs<br>        &emsp;- 3 GB of GPU RAM<br>        &emsp;- 5 GB disk "
"space<br>        &emsp;- 16 GB RAM<br>      "
msgstr ""
"        <b>限制</b><br>        以下限制适用：<br>        - 每个模拟的网格尺寸"
"限制为最多<b>2000万个网格单元</b><br>        - 不支持高性能计算：<br>        "
"&emsp;- 不支持GPU加速<br>        &emsp;- 不支持MPI多核加速<br>        - 不支"
"持第三方工具（例如，MUSAIK、SYSSIM、IMAnalytics等）<br>        - 无法添加额外"
"的ViP模型<br>        - 空闲30分钟后自动注销<br>        - 硬件资源限制"
"<br>        &emsp;- 3个CPU<br>        &emsp;- 3 GB的GPU内存<br>        "
"&emsp;- 5 GB的磁盘空间<br>        &emsp;- 16 GB的内存<br>      "

